class Solution {
    public int appendCharacters(String s, String t) {
        int sIndex = 0, tIndex = 0;
        while (sIndex < s.length() && tIndex < t.length()) {
            if (s.charAt(sIndex) == t.charAt(tIndex)) {
                tIndex++;
            }
            sIndex++;
        }
        return t.length() - tIndex;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates through both strings once, maintaining a pointer for each. It increments the pointer for string t only when a match is found with string s, effectively checking how much of t is a subsequence of s. The remaining characters in t that are not matched are the ones that need to be appended to s.
